      "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nNed,\nany chance to rename \"lustre/scripts/Lustre\" to something else?  It is playing havoc on MacOS with case-insensitive filesystems (the default for all Mac filesystems) because git thinks there is an unstaged diff due to the name clash with the existing \"lustre/scripts/lustre\" (lower-case ell) file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "05308135f6190b8937dfb32b72fcc2be98f7c500",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 126,
        "name": "Ned Bass",
        "email": "bass6@llnl.gov",
        "username": "nedbass"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-04 19:39:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nAndreas, we can do that.  I'm inclined to just move it into a subdirectory \"lustre/scripts/ha\" or somesuch, if that's OK with you.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "d0ddfda47f3963b0a2aa693fa2dff486f81b26f9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-06 15:16:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nNed, that would great, as long as \"Lustre\" and \"lustre\" are in separate directories afterward.  Brian had suggested including a \".ha_v2\" suffix or similar and adding a symlink in the .spec file at install time, so that when there are heartbeat v3 scripts they do not conflict.\n\nIn either case, it would be great to have something sooner rather than later, since this makes it difficult to use the repo as-is.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 10
    }
  ],
